headlines.description: — Miles Bridges had 26 points and 11 rebounds, Terry Rozier added 25 points and the Charlotte Hornets bounced back from an ugly loss to beat the Utah Jazz 107-101 on Friday night in front a sellout crowd.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges, Hornets bounce back with 107-101 win over Jazz

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis had 30 points and 10 rebounds and the Washington Wizards held on to beat the Detroit Pistons 100-97 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis has 30 points and 10 rebounds, Wizards top Pistons

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 33 points and 15 assists, Danilo Gallinari added 25 points and the Atlanta Hawks held on to beat the Golden State Warriors 121-110 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Gallinari power Hawks past Warriors, 121-110

events.name: New York Knicks at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Just when it looked as if the Miami Heat were going to open a little bit of breathing room atop the Eastern Conference, the New York Knicks had other ideas.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks close on 38-13 run, stun reeling Heat 111-103

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 20 points and nine rebounds and the Minnesota Timberwolves made up for a narrow loss at Dallas four days earlier by tightening up their defense and blowing out the Mavericks 116-95 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wolves stop skid, avenge recent loss with romp over Mavs

events.name: Houston Rockets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jalen Green had 23 points, including five 3-pointers, and the Houston Rockets built a big early lead before coasting to a 125-106 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green has 22, Rockets cruise to 125-106 win over Blazers

headlines.description: — Even after seeing James Harden and Joel Embiid record double-doubles in a convincing 25-point win over the Los Angeles Clippers on Friday night, Philadelphia 76ers coach Doc Rivers doesn't think his team is at its best yet.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden, Embiid have double-doubles, 76ers rout Clippers
